  "text": "To further analyze the roles of this kinesin in mitochondrial morphology at the cellular level, we generated polymerase chain reaction (PCR) primers to clone a cDNA coding for an ortholog of CeKLP-6 from rat tissues. Sequence analysis of the reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) products revealed a coding region for 1034 amino acid residues containing motor, forkhead-associated and three coiled-coil domains. Rat KLP6 (rKLP6) shares 53.8% and 26.9% sequence similarities with the motor and forkhead-associated domains of CeKLP-6, respectively ( Fig. 2A) . Comparative analysis showed that rKLP6 and its putative orthologs in vertebrates are uncharacterized kinesins and belong to the kinesin-3 family [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Anti-rKLP6 antibody specifically recognized a single 105-kDa protein in total cell lysates of rat PC-12 and human HeLa Fig. 2 . Characterization of rat KLP6. (A)Scheme of rat KLP6. Blue, purple and yellow boxes indicate motor, forkhead-associated (FHA) and coiled-coil (CC) domains, respectively. (B)Total cell lysates (80g proteins) from PC-12 and HeLa cells transfected with vector or the rKLP6 expression plasmids were subjected to immunoblotting with anti-rKLP6 antibody. (C)HeLa cells expressing rKLP6-3HA were fixed, permeabilized and immunostained with antibody to HA tag (a) and the mitochondrial outer membrane protein Tom20 (b). Images were acquired using confocal microscopy. Asterisks indicate cells expressing rKLP6-3HA. Scale bar: 10m. (D)The cell fractionation process. Total lysate from HeLa cells carrying the rKLP6-3HA expression plasmid was fractionated and separated into lowspeed pellet (LSP), high-speed pellet (HSP) and high-speed supernatant (HSS) fractions. The LSP fractions were further subjected to a 0, 20, 25 and 36% discontinuous density gradient of OptiPrep. The proteins migrating at the 0-20 and 20-25% interfaces were used as microsomal (Ms) and mitochondrial (Mt) fractions, respectively. These fractions were analyzed by immunoblotting with antibodies to rKLP6, the 39-kDa subunit of mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, the ER protein Sec61 and the cytosolic protein H450. cells (Fig. 2B ). An attempt to determine the intracellular distribution of endogenous KLP6 using the antibody was unsuccessful because of the low-level expression of KLP6. Because the expression of a C-terminally hemagglutinin (HA)-tagged rKLP6 (rKLP-3HA) did not influence mitochondrial morphology (Fig. 2C) , the association of KLP6 with mitochondria was analyzed in the rKLP-3HA-expressing cells. Cell fractionation indicated that rKLP6-3HA was mainly distributed in the cytoplasm, and was particularly associated with the endomembranes (Fig. 2D) . Flotation analysis using a discontinuous density gradient showed that rKLP6-3HA was cofractionated with mitochondria-enriched membranes (Fig. 2D , lane 5), suggesting that a fraction of KLP6 is associated with mitochondrial membranes.",
